node.text: TIPS FROM THE TOP: We’re finishing off our unexpected perfect pairs series with NARS Global Artistry Director @citizenjanes’s innovative combination for lit-from-within cheeks. On bare skin, “blend The Multiple in Copacabana over the entire cheek area, then complete the rest of your complexion. Once set, swirl the Yachiyo Brush over both shades of the Duo Eyeshadow in Kuala Lumpur and buff onto cheekbones.” According to Jane, “The cool tone of The Multiple allows the rose gold and boysenberry shades of Kuala Lumpur to come to life.” Swipe to see the final look.

node.text: TIPS FROM THE TOP: NARS Global Artistry Director @u.z.o has two surprising techniques for eyes that pop. For medium to deep skin tones: "Apply Velvet Matte Lip Pencil in Train Bleu to the entire eyelid and blend upwards to create a bold, smoky look. Then, apply Duo Eyeshadow in Kuala Lumpur for a shimmering effect." For light to medium skin tones, "apply Velvet Matte Lip Pencil in Good Times to the entire eyelid, layering the matte chestnut side of St Paul de Vence Duo Eyeshadow on top. For additional dimension, highlight the inner corners with the shimmering nectarine side of the eyeshadow duo." The Velvet Matte Lip Pencils “offer a creamier eyeshadow base,” Uzo adds. Swipe to explore both looks.
